Purpose
Define the approved technologies for Quant Hub, the rationale behind each choice, and the engineering principles governing future technology adoption.
Technology Selection Principles
Technologies are selected according to:• Long-term maintenance• Community maturity• Performance• Security• Documentation quality• Ecosystem support• AI-assisted development compatibility• Production readiness
Core Stack
Programming Language: PythonBackend Framework: FastAPIFrontend: Next.js + React + TypeScriptStyling: Tailwind CSSDatabase: PostgreSQLCache: RedisORM: SQLAlchemyData Validation: PydanticContainerization: DockerVersion Control: GitIDE: Visual Studio CodePrimary AI: Claude CodeEngineering MCP: Ruflo
Quantitative Libraries
NumPyPandasPolars (where performance is required)SciPyscikit-learnPyTorchXGBoostLightGBMTA-Lib (optional)VectorBTBacktesting.py (evaluation only)CCXTyfinance
Infrastructure
Discord for notifications.GitHub for source control.Environment variables for secrets.Docker for reproducible deployments.
Technology Governance
No new dependency may be introduced without documenting:• Purpose• Alternatives considered• Security implications• Maintenance expectations• Licensing compatibility
Future Technologies
Potential future additions:• Kubernetes• Apache Kafka• Ray• MLflow• Prometheus• Grafana• TimescaleDB• Apache Arrow• DuckDB
Closing
Technology choices should support the architecture instead of dictating it. Stability, maintainability, and extensibility take precedence over trend adoption.